# Python
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.pyo
.pytest_cache/
*.egg-info/

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# data/ GIT POLICY (P3-3, 2026-06-26)
#
# RUNTIME-ONLY (ignored — transient per-run churn, NEVER canonical, self-created
#   by code if absent; baking these into history is pure noise):
#     - data/*.json, data/**/*.json   → all live state snapshots & per-run reports
#       (incl. data/daily_report_*.json, data/milestones/*, data/daily_summaries/*,
#        data/monthly_reports/*, data/reports/* — all JSON, covered here)
#     - *.db / *.sqlite               → live DBs
#     - data/*.db-journal             → SQLite rollback journals (transient)
#     - data/backups/                 → daily DB backup snapshots
#     - data/*.jsonl                  → append-only runtime audit/hash-chain logs
#                                       (audit_trail.jsonl etc.; self-create on miss)
#
# OWNER-GATED DECISION (LEFT TRACKED ON PURPOSE — do NOT untrack without owner):
#   data/equity_curve_daily.json, data/golive_status.json,
#   data/paper_evidence_history.json are CURRENTLY committed track snapshots that
#   the site static-fallback may rely on. They ARE matched by the data/*.json rule
#   above but remain tracked because they were committed before this rule. Whether
#   the volatile track snapshots should live in git at all (canonical-in-git vs
#   runtime-only) is an OWNER decision — see CLAUDE.md "data/ git policy".
#   These were deliberately NOT `git rm --cached`'d here.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# P4-9 funding deep-history cache (RUNTIME-ONLY — explicit per owner-flag): the 5-venue funding
# median is persisted/merged across fetches into these files so the hedged-sleeve + rates-desk
# backtest replay window GROWS beyond a single keyless fetch. It can get large and self-creates
# on first refresh — NEVER commit it (keep it out of git history, like all of data/). Already
# matched by the data/*.json rule below, but pinned here so the policy is explicit.
data/funding_history_cache.json
data/funding_history_cache_*.json

# Data files (runtime, не в git)
data/*.json
data/**/*.json
*.db
*.sqlite
data/*.db-journal
data/backups/
data/*.jsonl
data/**/*.jsonl
logs/*.log
*.log
/tmp/

